text: Funa is a genus of sea snails, marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pseudomelatomidae. ==Species== Species within the genus Funa include: * Funa asra Kilburn, 1988 * Funa cretea Li B.Q., Kilburn & Li X.Z., 2010 * Funa fourlinniei Bozzetti, 2007 * Funa fraterculus Kilburn, 1988 * Funa hadra Sysoev & Bouchet, 2001 * Funa jeffreysii (E. A. Smith, 1875) * Funa laterculoides (Barnard, 1958) * Funa latisinuata (Smith E. A., 1877) * Funa spectrum (Reeve, 1845) (nomen dubium) * Funa tayloriana (Reeve, 1846) * Funa theoreta (Melvill, 1899) ;Species brought into synonymy: * Funa flavidula (Lamarck, 1822)(Lamarck, 1822) * Funa formidabilis (Hedley, 1922): synonym of Inquisitor formidabilis Hedley, 1922 ==References== ==External links== * * Bouchet, P.; Kantor, Y. I.; Sysoev, A.; Puillandre, N. (2011). A new operational classification of the Conoidea (Gastropoda). Journal of Molluscan Studies. 77(3): 273–308 Category:Pseudomelatomidae Category:Gastropod genera
title: Funa (gastropod)
